    <!-- Basics Section -->
    <section class="section" id="basics">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Resume Basics</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Before diving into the details, let's understand what a resume is, why it matters, and the fundamental principles of creating an effective one.</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What is a Resume?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>A resume is a concise document that summarizes your education, skills, experiences, and achievements. It's your personal marketing tool designed to showcase your qualifications for a specific job or opportunity.</p>
                        <p>Think of it as your professional highlight reel—a carefully curated collection of your most relevant accomplishments and abilities.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i> Purpose of a Resume</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The primary goal of your resume is to:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Get you an interview opportunity</li>
                            <li>Demonstrate your qualifications for a position</li>
                            <li>Differentiate you from other candidates</li>
                            <li>Provide talking points for interviews</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Remember: Recruiters typically spend only 6-7 seconds scanning a resume initially!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Resume Formats</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>There are three main resume formats:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Chronological:</strong> Lists work history in reverse chronological order (most recent first). Best for those with steady work history.</li>
                            <li><strong>Functional:</strong> Emphasizes skills over work history. Good for career changers or those with gaps.</li>
                            <li><strong>Combination:</strong> Blends both approaches. Ideal for highlighting both skills and experience.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>For students and beginners, a chronological or combination format usually works best.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>Pro Tip: One Page Rule</h4>
                <p>For students and early career professionals, keep your resume to one page. Recruiters appreciate conciseness, and it forces you to include only the most relevant information.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Resume Sections -->
    <section class="section" id="sections">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Essential Resume Sections</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">A well-structured resume contains several key sections. Let's break down each one and learn how to craft them effectively.</p>
            
            <div class="accordion">
                <div class="accordion-item active">
                    <div class="accordion-header">Contact Information</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>Your contact section should be prominently placed at the top of your resume and include:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Full Name:</strong> Use a slightly larger font to make it stand out</li>
                                <li><strong>Phone Number:</strong> Make sure it's one you actually answer</li>
                                <li><strong>Professional Email Address:</strong> Ideally firstname.lastname@domain.com</li>
                                <li><strong>Location:</strong> City and state/province is sufficient (full address not necessary)</li>
                                <li><strong>LinkedIn Profile:</strong> Customize your URL (linkedin.com/in/yourname)</li>
                                <li><strong>Portfolio/GitHub:</strong> If relevant to your field</li>
                            </ul>
                            
                            <div class="example">
                                <h4 class="example-header">Example</h4>
                                <div class="example-content">
JOHN SMITH
Mumbai, Maharashtra | (91) 98765-43210 | john.smith@email.com
linkedin.com/in/johnsmith | github.com/johnsmith
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="warning">
                                <h4>Avoid These Mistakes</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Using unprofessional email addresses (partyanimal123@email.com)</li>
                                    <li>Including social media profiles that aren't professionally relevant</li>
                                    <li>Forgetting to update your contact information when it changes</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">Professional Summary/Objective</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>This 2-3 sentence section appears at the top of your resume and provides a quick overview of who you are professionally.</p>
                            
                            <h4>For students with limited experience (Objective):</h4>
                            <p>Focus on your education, relevant skills, and career goals.</p>
                            
                            <div class="example">
                                <h4 class="example-header">Example Objective</h4>
                                <div class="example-content">
Recent Computer Science graduate from IIT Mumbai with strong programming skills in Java and Python, seeking an entry-level Software Developer position to apply my knowledge of algorithms and data structures while growing my expertise in cloud technologies.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <h4>For those with some experience (Summary):</h4>
                            <p>Highlight your most relevant experiences and key accomplishments.</p>
                            
                            <div class="example">
                                <h4 class="example-header">Example Summary</h4>
                                <div class="example-content">
Detail-oriented Marketing student with 2 years of internship experience in social media management and content creation. Demonstrated success in increasing engagement by 45% for a campus organization through strategic campaigns. Skilled in Adobe Creative Suite and Google Analytics.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="tip">
                                <h4>Customize for Each Application</h4>
                                <p>Tailor your summary/objective to match the specific job you're applying for by incorporating keywords from the job description.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">Education</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>For students and recent graduates, the education section is particularly important and should be placed prominently on your resume.</p>
                            
                            <h4>What to Include:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Degree and Major:</strong> Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science</li>
                                <li><strong>University Name:</strong> Indian Institute of Technology, Mumbai</li>
                                <li><strong>Graduation Date:</strong> Expected May 2024 (or Month Year if completed)</li>
                                <li><strong>GPA:</strong> Include if it's 3.0/4.0 (or 7.5/10) or higher</li>
                                <li><strong>Relevant Coursework:</strong> List 4-6 courses most relevant to the job</li>
