    <!-- Resume Writing Tips -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Resume Writing Tips</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Follow these proven strategies to make your resume more effective and professional.</p>
            
            <div class="steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <h3>Use Action Verbs</h3>
                    <p>Begin each bullet point with a strong action verb to create impact and show initiative.</p>
                    <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Developed, Implemented, Coordinated, Analyzed, Created, Managed, Led, Designed</p>
                    <div class="example">
                        <h4 class="example-header">Instead of:</h4>
                        <div class="example-content">
"Was responsible for managing social media accounts"
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="example">
                        <h4 class="example-header">Write:</h4>
                        <div class="example-content">
"Managed 5 social media accounts, increasing follower engagement by 45% in 3 months"
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3>Quantify Achievements</h3>
                    <p>Use numbers, percentages, and specific metrics to demonstrate the impact of your work.</p>
                    <div class="example">
                        <h4 class="example-header">Instead of:</h4>
                        <div class="example-content">
"Helped increase website traffic"
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="example">
                        <h4 class="example-header">Write:</h4>
                        <div class="example-content">
"Implemented SEO strategies that increased website traffic by 65% over 4 months"
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3>Tailor to Each Job</h3>
                    <p>Customize your resume for each position by matching your qualifications to the job requirements.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Analyze the job description for keywords and required skills</li>
                        <li>Reorganize your resume to highlight the most relevant experiences</li>
                        <li>Adjust your professional summary to align with the specific role</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="tip">
                        <h4>ATS Optimization</h4>
                        <p>Many companies use Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS) to screen resumes. Include relevant keywords from the job description to ensure your resume passes these automated filters.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3>Focus on Design and Formatting</h3>
                    <p>Create a clean, professional layout that's easy to scan.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use consistent formatting for headings, bullet points, and spacing</li>
                        <li>Choose a professional, readable font (Arial, Calibri, Garamond)</li>
                        <li>Use 10-12 point font size for body text, 14-16 for headings</li>
                        <li>Include sufficient white space to avoid a cluttered appearance</li>
                        <li>Use bold, italics, and underlining sparingly for emphasis</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="warning">
                        <h4>Avoid These Design Mistakes</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Fancy graphics or images (unless you're in a creative field)</li>
                            <li>Excessive colors or decorative fonts</li>
                            <li>Tables or text boxes that might confuse ATS systems</li>
                            <li>Cramming too much information onto the page</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3>Proofread Thoroughly</h3>
                    <p>Errors on your resume can immediately disqualify you from consideration.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Check for spelling, grammar, and punctuation errors</li>
                        <li>Verify that all dates, company names, and titles are accurate</li>
                        <li>Ensure consistent formatting throughout the document</li>
                        <li>Have someone else review your resume for feedback</li>
                        <li>Read your resume out loud to catch awkward phrasing</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="tip">
                        <h4>Proofreading Tools</h4>
                        <p>Use tools like Grammarly or Hemingway Editor to catch errors and improve readability, but don't rely solely on automated tools.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mistake">
                <h4>Common Resume Mistakes to Avoid</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Including an objective that's too generic</strong> - Customize it for each position</li>
                    <li><strong>Using a one-size-fits-all resume</strong> - Tailor it to each job application</li>
                    <li><strong>Including irrelevant information</strong> - Focus on what matters for the specific role</li>
                    <li><strong>Being too modest</strong> - Highlight your achievements confidently</li>
                    <li><strong>Using personal pronouns</strong> - Avoid "I," "me," or "my" in your resume</li>
                    <li><strong>Including references</strong> - Save space by providing these only when requested</li>
                    <li><strong>Lying or exaggerating</strong> - Be honest about your qualifications and experiences</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

