    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section" id="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Answers to common questions about resume building for students and beginners.</p>
            
            <div class="accordion">
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">How long should my resume be?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>For students and early career professionals, stick to one page. This forces you to include only the most relevant information and respects recruiters' limited time. Only extend to two pages if you have substantial relevant experience that directly relates to the position.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">What if I don't have any work experience?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>Focus on other relevant experiences:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Academic projects:</strong> Course assignments, research, thesis work</li>
                                <li><strong>Volunteer work:</strong> Community service, non-profit contributions</li>
                                <li><strong>Campus activities:</strong> Student organizations, leadership roles</li>
                                <li><strong>Personal projects:</strong> Websites, apps, or other initiatives you've created</li>
                                <li><strong>Relevant coursework:</strong> Classes that taught you applicable skills</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Emphasize transferable skills from these experiences that relate to the job you're seeking.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">Should I include a photo on my resume?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>In most countries including India, it's generally not recommended to include a photo on your resume unless specifically requested. Photos can potentially lead to unconscious bias in the hiring process. Focus on your qualifications rather than appearance.</p>
                            <p>Exceptions may exist for certain creative fields or international applications where photos are customary (some European countries and parts of Asia).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">How do I explain gaps in my resume?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>Be honest but strategic about gaps:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>If you took time for education or skill development, mention this</li>
                                <li>For gaps due to personal reasons, you can briefly explain in your cover letter (not resume)</li>
                                <li>Focus on what you learned or accomplished during the gap period</li>
                                <li>Consider using a functional resume format that emphasizes skills over chronology</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Remember that short gaps (a few months) often don't require explanation, especially for students transitioning between academic periods.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">How do I make my resume stand out?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>Make your resume stand out through content and presentation:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Quantify achievements</strong> with specific numbers and metrics</li>
                                <li><strong>Customize</strong> each resume for the specific job</li>
                                <li><strong>Use industry keywords</strong> relevant to your target position</li>
                                <li><strong>Include unique projects or experiences</strong> that demonstrate initiative</li>
                                <li><strong>Ensure perfect formatting</strong> with consistent styling and no errors</li>
                                <li><strong>Focus on results</strong> rather than just responsibilities</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Remember that standing out comes from demonstrating your unique value, not from gimmicks or unusual designs (unless you're in a creative field).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header">How often should I update my resume?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>Update your resume regularly:</p>
